\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 The Vaughn Group's office, perched on the fourth floor at Wabash and Lake in downtown Chicago, boasts a modern, uncluttered 5,000 square-foot layout. A welcoming entrance leads to a sleek interior, where offices and conference rooms line the periphery, and cubicles fill the core. Decorated with monochromatic photographs of Chicago's iconic architecture and bridges and motivational posters, the office blends business with artistry. A standout feature is the "Inspiration" conference room, adorned with a vibrant abstract painting by Liz's friend Chloe, offering a colorful contrast and serving as a creative muse for the team.}
