\par\pard\plain \tx0\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch \f0\fs26\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 Liz}{\f2\fs26\b1\i0  }{\f4\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 (Inquisitive, concerned):}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So you\u8217\'92re still going through with your one-year relationship plan?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 Evan}{\f2\fs26\b1\i0  }{\f4\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 (Sincere):}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes. I admit I had my doubts after our first date. She is such a great girl, and I don\u8217\'92t want to hurt her. But after spending so much time with her this week, I really feel this could be something good. But I was still on the fence until earlier today.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 Liz}{\f2\fs26\b1\i0  }{\f4\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 (Curious):}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What happened earlier today?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 Evan}{\f2\fs26\b1\i0  }{\f4\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 (Informative response):}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I spoke to Guido. Although he thinks I should drop this plan and be his wingman, he said I can\u8217\'92t do this plan half-ass \endash  either I\u8217\'92m all in or all out. He made me realize that allowing my apprehension and guilty conscience into the relationship is of no benefit to Maggie or myself.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 Liz}{\f2\fs26\b1\i0  }{\f4\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 (Supportive, concerned):}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Although I\u8217\'92d rather you not pursue this plan of yours, I\u8217\'92m glad you decided not to be Guido\u8217\'92s \u8216\'91wingman.\u8217\'92\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 Evan}{\f2\fs26\b1\i0  }{\f4\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 (Sincere, well-meaning):}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It wasn\u8217\'92t just Guido\u8217\'92s advice that convinced me. After thinking about it, I realize I would never have met Maggie without this plan. She lives far away and doesn\u8217\'92t belong to any dating sites. I figure maybe it was meant to be, no matter how it turns out. She may not be my true love, but I\u8217\'92m going to push aside my fears and guilt and give her the best that I have to offer. After all, she deserves it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b1\i0\cf5 Liz}{\f2\fs26\b1\i0  }{\f4\fs26\b0\i1\cf4 (Concerned Evan won\loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8217\'92t give his feelings for Maggie a chance to blossom):}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Well, Evan, I promised to support you, and I will. I only ask one favor. Be open to letting love in. I\u8217\'92m not suggesting you force it; you can\u8217\'92t fake love. But I think a year will be enough time to know your true feelings for Maggie. And I\u8217\'92m convinced if your feelings for her grow into love, you\u8217\'92ll abandon your plan to break up. But, if you don\u8217\'92t fall in love with her, as much as I hate to admit it, letting go will be the right thing to do. \u8221\'94}
